This is a nice map for GunGame, aim training, regular, skill training, and whatever.
I love this map. The colors, the shaping, the lights, it makes it kind of magic. That is why I named the map "bluemagic".

The map has different ways to go, and it fits sniping, close combats, SMG-wars, and so on. :)

It has two buyzones, and there are two floors; one up in the open, and one under ground, like caves, with a modern look.

There is a lot of boxes and stuff to hide behind, and the spawn areas is pretty far way from each other, so no annoying, rushing newfag will take you out before you even get to by yourself a gun. The spawn areas is on the lower floor, and the spawn areas are hidden behind some boxes and walls, so when you get "out in the air", it's like a fog of magic and mystery is approaching you, witch is what I like about the map.

The lights makes beautiful patterns in the roof, on the walls and floor, so the map is very lovely to play.

Please send me a message if you're going to host my map on your server, I would love to play it with as many as possible!

Peace out, and more nice maps will be created!

By the way, this is my first map I shown in public, so please add a comment!

ENJ0y!

PS: I made some differenses from 1.0 :)

BF2_CSS_models.bsp Read Me
Map by Arrogant Orange(in game name: MIR\/EN-131)
To use with:Counter-Strike: SOURCE
Made with: SOURCE SDK
Version: 1.0/ Status: Functional

=================================================

Contents of folder:
1x BF2_CSS_models.bsp map file
1x BF2_CSS_models.nav BOT Navigation file
3x Screen Shots
1x BF2_CSS_modelsReadme.txt file

=================================================

Map Story: 

BF2_CSS_models.bsp is themed in a Gladiators like style. Where fighters come to play for money while people who bet on and watch the games come to enjoy their blood get shed.

Map description:

BF2_CSS_models.bsp was supposed to be my attempt at modeling a few models from Battlefield 2 but instead I ended up designing a Fight-Yrad map for CS:S with the only two(2) models a managed to recreate. The Counter-Terrorists start in a fortified base while the Terrorists start out in the basement(I need to re-render the map in a future version cause currently the BOT's don't know how to leave the basement. So I had to move the T-spawns to the upper outside.)of an old hut.  The map has two(2)sniper spots equipped with a single AWP each. There are varying amounts of cover scattered around the map. Mortar fire is live, lethal and on going. Also there are a few visible mines between both of the force's spawn zones. The viewing stands can be accessed threw the closet in the building facing the CT Spawn zone. You can purchase weapons threw the Buy-menu or pick them up in various places around the map. All side arms are available in both spawn zones as well as an MP5 crate and an M16 in the CT-Spawn and an AK-47 crate in the T-Spawn. Grenades can be picked up from the chest in both the spawn zones as well. 

=================================================

Bugs/ Known Issues:

+The map is missing a few different bits of detail here and there.
+Some of the terrain isn't lined up correctly.
+One mine occasionally blows up when hit by a mortar round(ballistics will not trip the mines!)
+Um...oh the lighting sucks, as always X)
+You have to continuously hold crouch when useing the tunnel that extends from the hut basement to the outpost.

=================================================

_sText:
This map is the 2nd in hopefully several other maps that will come after.

It is part of project- ''Wintermaze_2016'' that im working on. 

Player count; 20vs20

Now I know what you think...''It's a goddamn maze!!''. Think of it more like a maze like structure. A series of protective walls to prevent the player from getting sniped. My goal here is not to get the player lost in the maze! 

I hope that you will enjoy the gameplay and have fun! :)

And remember! 

When swimming in pipes always look up! 

Feel free to comment and by all means let me know if you find any bugs or other issues of the map.

_aChangeLog.text: Radar on top left corner (will be easier to not get lost)
Changed the shape of windows and wall to improve on rendering, and reduce unneeded geometry
Removed incorrect optimization tools- hints and occluders (back then I didn't know how to correctly use them)
Neatly packed everything in .bsp instead of seperate folders
